'''Prejish Prakash''' ([[Malayalam]] '''പ്രജീഷ് പ്രകാശ്''') is an [[Indian people|Indian]] [[film editor]] working primarily in [[Malayalam cinema]]. He is also a [[web designer]] and an [[entrepreneur]]. 
Other than feature-film editing he edited various [[documentaries]], [[advertisements]], [[Corporate video]]s, Film [[Trailer (promotion)]] etc. in his career. 
<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6293287/</ref>

==Early life and education ==
Prejish Prakash was born on 24 February 1986 in [[Pathanamthitta]] to a [[Christians|Christian]] family. He did his schooling from [[Mount Bethany EHSS]],<ref>http://www.schoollistindia.com/mount-bethany-ehss-mylapra-pathanamthitta_1030149-kl.html/</ref> and graduate with a degree in [[Multimedia]] from [[St Joseph College of Communication]] in 2007.<ref>http://www.sjcc.edu.in/</ref>

== Editing career ==
He began his editing career by joining Yes [[indiavision]] Satellite Communications as a [[video editor]] in 2008.<ref>http://www.yesindiavision.com/</ref> His passion towards movies and film editing lead him to step into the film industry. He worked as an associate editor with the editors VT Sreejith and [[Arun Kumar Aravind]]  in various movies.

Prejish started working as an independent film editor in the film [[Mullassery Madhavan Kutty Nemom P. O.]] in 2012.

In 2013, Prejish edited the movie [[Philips and the monkey pen]] which completed 111 days in theaters and was a huge commercial success at the box-office.<ref>http://www.kerala9.com/event/philips-and-the-monkey-pen-movie-111th-day-celebration-photos</ref> This film also won the [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Children's Film]], [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Child Artist]]<ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Kerala-state-film-awards</ref> and Kerala State Film Award for Best Children's Film Director.

Movie [[vedivazhipadu]] 2013 was his next editorial venture which was the maiden production venture of [[Arun Kumar Aravind]].<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/vedivazhipadu-starts-rolling-news-malayalam-nhilMfajfbb.html</ref> Prejish edited the [[psychological thriller]] movie [[1 by Two]] in 2014 directed by [[Arun Kumar Aravind]] and written by [[Jeyamohan]]<ref>http://movieorange.com/?topic=detail&category=Review&article=5356580d4a112</ref>

In 2015 he started a new media firm named "Culte Media & Entertainment Network" in [[Cochin]] with state of the art post production facilities for film editing.<ref>http://www.culte.in/team.html</ref> In 2018 the firm is rebranded to "Peppino Studios". Lead by the team from Peppino Studios, started a film & Video editing training centre also named "School Of Editing".<ref>http://schoolofediting.com/about-school-of-editing/</ref>

